My journey so far. What will yours be? 

I’m sharing this to brag- but to give you perspective.

When you lose everything it’s easy to think that it’s all over now. But often, it’s just the beginning of something so much better that you never thought possible!

So don’t feel down too long - celebrate what happened so you can move forward with full focus!

And if you feel like having a fresh start with a business,

node.text:
What do Jeff Bezos, Elon Musk, Bill Gates and all other people have in common?

They all have 24 hours in a day.

So do you, so do I.

We all have an equal amount of time.

So how come that some of us are billionaires, and some not?

Well, it’s not about how much time we have, it’s how we use the time.

How focused are you on your goals?

How much of your time do you really use to work on your dreams?

Now that you remember what you really want to work on…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

node.text:
It hurts me to see this…

People with amazing jobs and $300k a year salaries…

Lose everything the moment they lose their job.

Because the moment their salary is gone, so is their lifestyle and living standard.

Their success is tied to their job.

Working a job, buying a house and being happy forever worked 50 years ago.

But times have changed.

To make it in today’s world you need to make your money work for you.

In other words: invest.

If you are just starting out, it’s best to invest in yourself and your skills.

Want to start investing and break into a beginner friendly side-hustle?

follow 👉@bjkuniversity

node.text:
When a fire ate away my restaurant business, I was devastated.

I wasn’t very good at running a restaurant. In fact, I was so broke I couldn’t pay the insurance, so I lost it completely.

But running a restaurant was the only thing I knew how to do back then.

I knew I had to improve my skill level and turn my life around.

So, I took a course on how to sell on Amazon.

I put in time and effort, and after 5 years, I’d made it.

Selling on Amazon is definitely for serious people only.

It’s easier to start compared to many other businesses…

But it’s still a business.

Yet, if you are willing to put in time and effort, you’ll reap the rewards.

If you think you got what it takes…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

...to get started.

node.text:
Read THIS if you want to be successful.

For any goal you have in life, it’s very important who you take advice from.
Most people fail because they listen to the wrong people.

Filtering advice from family and friends can be hard because you love them and you know they mean well.

But the thing is, they aren’t you!

They don’t live your life and they don’t have the same goals as you.

Same goes for your neighbors.

Most of them just want to gossip about you.

They have little impact on your life at all, so why listen to them?

So, the next time you receive advice ask yourself:

“Is this person living the life I want?”

If the answer is “no”, thank them for their advice but don’t follow it.

Instead, start looking for people who achieved what you want to achieve and model what they are doing.

For example, if you want to start your own business or side hustle, and want to successfully sell online…

follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

… for the best advice.

node.text:
“You are just lazy” 😔 

When you are exhausted it looks to others like you aren’t doing much.

They call you lazy and unmotivated…

Because they don’t know what’s going on inside you.

I truly believe you aren’t lazy. It’s okay to reach a point where you feel like you can’t go on.

But you owe it to yourself that you never give up.

So, take a break. 

Take a step back and remember why you started…

And then get right back at it.

You got this! 👊

If you are looking for a new, fulfilling thing to do…
